reviewText: It was interesting to watch these different kinds of movies. Loved to see how the importance the bible is displayed. The picture quality of the older movies is pretty bad at times. Nevertheless it is great to see the beauty of unspoiled nature. "Nothing to good for a cowboy" it not really a movie for children, I did enjoy watching how Gloria and Rich stand up for one another. Yes and how Rich respects the importance of marriage.
My mother in law wanted this DVD with many movies of her liking and is happy with it.  Arrived in great condition.
Enjoyed different episodes and were good family entertainment.  Had seen some before but good value for the price. Whole family could watch.

My jaw dropped when I saw this DVD available on Amazon. The Daughters of Joshua Cabe has NEVER been available in ANY way whatsoever. This movie along with The Young Pioneers were both ABC Movies of the Week.
Watching them really bought back wonderful memories.
I have yet to watch the other movies that are on these 2 discs, but I will watch them soon.
If you have been as anxious as I have to find the 2 movies I mentioned then don't hesitate to get this DVD.
So happy to finally have these movies.
I'm hoping that I start to see more movies of the week available on Amazon.
Especially THE FEMINIST & THE FUZZ with Barbara Eden.
These movies are older than i expected but are great family movies. I made this purchase because the collection was a great price.

This collection of movies is great.  I highly recommend the collection.  One of the movies introduces Helen Hunt as a child.  That's my favorite of all these movies (Pioneer Woman), although the others are wonderful too.

I had been looking for years for the the Young Pioneers movie that I saw all those years ago.  After reading one of the posts on Amazon, I bought this movie.  So far only have watched Young Pioneers, but look forward to watching the other movies on these DVDs.
The quality of the movies were very bad. the contents  fair
Some of the movie seem ok but Seven Alone is not one of them . The color is so faded you can't see it very well sky and people and mountains blend together . Bad copy on that one .
Great movies

I bought this set for the "Young Pioneers" movie.  I was not disappointed in this movie at all.  It was nice, good, clean television.  Some of the others in this collection were duds for me.  But, given the low price, I'm a happy camper that the main movie I wanted to see was great.
The quality of most of the films in this collection was abysmal making them hard to watch and their stories difficult to follow.  It was a disappointing purchase.
Great for the whole family!

I'm happy to have all the movies, however the only movie I've watched so far is "Seven Alone". The story is nice but I had a hard time seeing it - I adjusted the tv settings and still had problems.  I've not had to do this with too many other movies.  Looking forward to watching the other movies when I get time though.

Like most in these types of sets there is always one or two really good movies and one that is just passable and the others worth watching.
Having said that there are 8 movies for the entire family to watch and there are no worries of inappropriate content in any of them. it is worth buying though. Maybe being an adult some seemed a little lame. But perhaps some younger viewers and small children would enjoy those more. I purchase these type of multi-pack movies to pass on to people you are recovering from illnesses or injuries. So my opinion is not the utmost priority when I decide to purchase.
Very good movies.
Oldies but goodies. Good family story telling
